snippet.textDisplay:
But it would take more force to throw the golden gauntlet block than to just lift it! Calculate the height he threw it, then use gravitational potential energy = mgh and that kinetic energy = 0.5mv^2 to solve for the velocity it must have been when it left his hands. Then you can solve for the imparted momentum of the block and time the lift to find the necessary impulse and finally find the force needed

also, it looks like the block falls at a rate unbefitting a planet with g = 9.80665 ms/^2, so redo your calculations for a planet like Neptune (g =~ 14.07)
snippet.textOriginal:
